<!--
VOICING PLAN:
- Pickup + mm. 1–4: Light I-vi-V-I-IV patterns. RH 2-note pairs, LH 3-note open voicings. Root pos and 1st inv alternating.
- mm. 5–8: I and V patterns; m6 V ascending single-note RH arpeggio for variety; m8 V7 with C# for secondary color.
- mm. 9–12: vi → V modal digression; m9 vi7 with LH D4 top note; m11 IV quartal RH.
- mm. 13–16: IV-ii-V-I resolution; m14 V7 with C#3 in LH (rich bass); m16 pedal D1 for final cadence.

VOICE LEADING HIGHLIGHTS:
- m1→m2: LH B3 (vi top) → A3 (V root) steps down smoothly
- m6: single-note RH arpeggio contrasts the block chords elsewhere; LH builds beatwise
- m9→m10: LH D4 (vi 7th) → C#4 (V 7th) → D3 (I root) converges inward
- m15→m16: contrary motion — RH steps down A→F#, LH steps up A3→D3

TEXTURE ARC:
- Pickup-m4: sparse, 2-note RH, 3-note LH — tender opening
- mm. 5–8: moderate, climbing RH arpeggio at m6 adds forward motion
- mm. 9–11: fuller LH (4 notes), vi7 adds color at m9
- mm. 12–16: full body with V7 bass richness; final pedal D1 for pedal harp grandeur
-->
